Whisk vinegar, mustard, oregano, salt and pepper in a small bowl. Gradually whisk in oil to make a thick dressing; set aside. Cook the pasta in a large pot of salted boiling water until al dente. Drain, and cool slightly; toss with dressing. In a large bowl, combine the salami, pepperoni, Asiago cheese, olives, red peppers and artichokes. Add pasta to salad ingredients; toss and serve.